chunk_content: For OVC entered as “Reported HIV-negative to IP” in a previous reporting period - if the IP believes the child’s risk has not changed in the last 6 months, they should continue to report the child as HIV-negative during the current reporting period. However, if the IP believes that the child has recently been exposed to risk of HIV infection (e.g., sexual violence) or if an adolescent has become sexually active, then the IP should conduct an HIV risk assessment.
